\begin_layout Proposition
The estimator is in general not consistent when data is missing at random,
 even when raters are exchangeable.
 Moreover,
 the standard errors calculated using the usual machinery are correct.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Remark
A weaker condition but arguably useless condition suffices for consistency with exchangeable raters.
 See the proof for details.
